  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Physical activity is thought to increase overall body functions and to decrease
      cardiovascular and stroke risk factors. Now the question arose, wether enhanced exercise
      could also exert positive influence on cognition in the aging brain. Therefore, 50 to 80
      years old healthy subjects take part in a prospective study with regular sports activity
      during 6 months. Cognitive functions are detected with sensitive neuropsychological outcome
      measures, further investigations include MRT of the head, lactat- and other physical measures
      as well as detailed serum profiles. As a hypothesis, enhanced physical activity is suggested
      to predict better cognitive performance.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
